[{"location":"#AlphaShapes.jl-Documentation","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Overview-of-AlphaShapes.jl","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"Overview of AlphaShapes.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Alpha-Shapes","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"Alpha Shapes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"An alpha-shape is closely related to the Delaunay triangulation and Convex Hull of a set of points (in any dimension).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"The alpha-shape is constructed for a parameter alpha by testing each Delaunay simplex to determine if it's circumsphere has a radius less than alpha. If it does then the simplex is kept, otherwise the simplex is removed. This modified triangulation is the alpha-shape.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"Choosing alpha is done in many ways. AlphaShapes.jl optimises alpha to find the triangulation with the smallest volume which includes all input points as a vertex to at least on simplex.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"A mathematical reference","category":"page"},{"location":"#Functionality","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"Functionality","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"AlphaShapes.jl represents an alpha-shape as a function of an array, Array{Float64,2}, of points. So all user functionality comes through this.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"AlphaShape","category":"page"},{"location":"#AlphaShapes.AlphaShape","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.AlphaShape","text":"AlphaShape(X::Array{Float64,2};α::Union{Nothing,Float64}=nothing,\n    search::Tuple{Float64,Float64}=(0.0, 10.0),\n    MaxSteps::Int=100)::Array{Float64,3}\n\nFind the alpha shape corresponding to the 2D array of points X: [npoints,2], and the α value α.\n\nIf α == nothing then a search over the range of values search is done to find the best value. The optimisation objective is the alpha shape area (minimise) subject to all points in X being included in the alpha shape triangulation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Utils","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"Utils","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"The volume of one simplex can be found using","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"AlphaShapes.SimplexVolume","category":"page"},{"location":"#AlphaShapes.SimplexVolume","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.SimplexVolume","text":"SimplexVolume\n\nCalculate the volume of a simplex using the Cayley Menger matrix\n\nhttps://westy31.home.xs4all.nl/Circumsphere/ncircumsphere.htm\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"For the whole alpha-shape the volume can be found using","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"AlphaShapes.AlphaShapeVolume","category":"page"},{"location":"#AlphaShapes.AlphaShapeVolume","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.AlphaShapeVolume","text":"AlphaShapeVolume(A::Array{Float64,3})\n\nreturn the sum of volumes of all simplices in the alpha shapes A\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"The Delaunay triangulation is used to build the alpha shapes so there is a helper method to build one for any set of points (MiniQhull.jl)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"AlphaShapes.GetDelaunayTriangulation","category":"page"},{"location":"#AlphaShapes.GetDelaunayTriangulation","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.GetDelaunayTriangulation","text":"GetDelaunayTriangulation(points::Array{Float64,2})::Array{Float64,3}\n\nWrap MiniQhull.jl's delaunay to get a delaunay triangualation in any dimension\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#Under-the-hood","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"Under the hood","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"Arbitrary dimensions is handled by using the Cayley-Menger matrix for simplex volume and simplex circumsphere calculation","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"AlphaShapes.CayleyMenger\nAlphaShapes.SimplexCircumSphere","category":"page"},{"location":"#AlphaShapes.CayleyMenger","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.CayleyMenger","text":"    CayleyMenger\n\nCompute the Cayley-Menger matrix from squared\ndistances dij^2.\n\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/Cayley-MengerDeterminant.html\n\nFor a 2-d triangle the following example would symbolically\nrepresent the matrix for points x1, x2, and x3 where dij^2\nis the square Euclidean distance between i and j\nExample\n\njulia>:([0    1      1      1\n         1    0      d12^2  d13^2\n         1    d21^2  0      d23^2\n         1    d32^2  d32^2    0])\n:([0 1 1 1; 1 0 d12 ^ 2 d13 ^ 2; 1 d21 ^ 2 0 d23 ^ 2; 1 d32 ^ 2 d32 ^ 2 0])\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#AlphaShapes.SimplexCircumSphere","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.SimplexCircumSphere","text":"SimplexCircumSphere\n\nFind the centre and radius of the circumsphere of a simplex https://westy31.home.xs4all.nl/Circumsphere/ncircumsphere.htm\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#contents","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"contents","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#Index","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","title":"AlphaShapes.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"page"}]
